  "response": "This is an interesting research question. While I'm not aware of a definitive comprehensive study that has conclusively mapped out snacking differences across movie genres, there are some potential psychological and behavioral factors that might influence snacking preferences:\n\n1. Emotional state during different movie genres:\n- Horror movies might lead to more nervous or anxious snacking\n- Comedy movies might encourage more relaxed, social snacking\n\n2. Potential research considerations:\n- Stress levels during different movie types\n- Comfort food preferences\n- Eating as a coping mechanism\n\nTo definitively answer this, a specific scientific study would need to:\n- Control for variables\n- Use a representative sample\n- Measure snack types and quantities\n- Analyze psychological and physiological responses\n\nCurrent evidence is mostly anecdotal, and while intriguing, more research would be needed to draw solid conclusions about genre-specific snacking behaviors.\n\nWould you be interested in potential research methodologies to explore this question?",
